1. *Biram* najbolje opcije za svoje putovanje. (I choose the best options for my trip.)
2. Ti *biraš* mesto gde ćemo večerati večeras. (You choose the place where we will have dinner tonight.)
3. Ona *bira* novu haljinu za proslavu. (She chooses a new dress for the celebration.)
4. Mi *biramo* najlepšu tortu za rođendansku proslavu. (We choose the most beautiful cake for the birthday party.)
5. *Biraću* druge boje zidova u sobi. (I will choose different colors for the walls in the room.)
6. Kada sam bio mlađi, uvek sam *birao* najbolje knjige za čitanje. (When I was younger, I always chose the best books to read.)
7. Vi ste *birali* pravi trenutak da me iznenadite. (You chose the right moment to surprise me.)
8. Oni će *birati* najbolje igračke za decu. (They will choose the best toys for children.)
9. *Biraj* između ovih dva sladoleda. (Choose between these two ice creams.)
10. Ja sam već *izabrao* koji film ćemo gledati večeras. (I have already chosen which movie we will watch tonight.)

Note: The word "biram" is the first person singular present tense form of the verb "birati" (to choose) in Serbian. The other forms used in the sentences are: "biraš" (second person singular present tense), "bira" (third person singular present tense), "biramo" (first person plural present tense), "biraću" (first person singular future tense), "birao" (past tense), "birali" (past tense plural), "birati" (infinitive), "biraj" (imperative singular), and "izabrao" (past tense singular masculine).